  "Allegations" : "SEC ADMINISTRATIVE RELEASE 34-57947; INVESTMENT ADVISERS RELEASE 40-2743; INVESTMENT COMPANY ACT RELEASE 40-28299, JUNE 11, 2008: THE SEC FILED AN ORDER INSTITUTING ADMINISTRATIVE AND CEASE-AND-DESIST PROCEEDINGS PURSUANT TO SECTIONS 15(B) AND 21C OF THE SECURITIES EXCHANGE ACT OF 1934, SECTION 203(F) OF THE INVESTMENT ADVISERS ACT OF 1940, AND SECTION 9(B) OF THE INVESTMENT COMPANY ACT OF 1940 (ORDER) AGAINST MICHAEL K. BRUGMAN (RESPONDENT).  THE ORDER ALLEGES THAT FROM MID-2001 THROUGH DECEMBER 2002, RESPONDENT, WHO WAS AT THAT TIME A SECURITIES SALESMAN, ACCEPTED PERSONAL PAYMENTS TOTALING OVER $3 MILLION FROM VARIOUS ENTITIES IN EXCHANGE FOR PROCURING MARKET TIMING CAPACITY WITH HIS EMPLOYING FIRM. THE ORDER FURTHER ALLEGES THAT RESPONDENT NEVER DISCLOSED THESE PAYMENTS TO THE FIRM EVEN THOUGH, AS ITS AGENT AND FIDUCIARY AND PURSUANT TO A WRITTEN AGREEMENT RESPONDENT HAD WITH FIRM, HE HAD A DUTY TO DO SO. AS A RESULT OF THIS CONDUCT, THE ORDER ALLEGES THAT RESPONDENT WILLFULLY VIOLATED SECTION 10(B) OF THE EXCHANGE ACT OF 1934 AND RULE 10B-5 THEREUNDER.",
